H0.text: The wood of which common tree was traditionally used to make tennis racquets, billiard cues and hockey sticks. Oak

H1.text: The wood of which common tree was traditionally used to make tennis racquets, billiard cues and hockey sticks. Maple

H2.text: The wood of which common tree was traditionally used to make tennis racquets, billiard cues and hockey sticks. Cherry

H3.text: The wood of which common tree was traditionally used to make tennis racquets, billiard cues and hockey sticks. Ash

A4.text: Good quality pool cues are customarily made from straight-grained hard rock maple wood, especially the shaft.

A5.text: Snooker cues, by contrast, are almost always made of ash wood.
